<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p><strong>By rail:</strong> King's is a 3-minute walk from Denmark Hill station (lifts to all platforms), and about a 12-minute walk from Loughborough Junction station (step access only). The nearest underground station is Brixton, which is a 10-minute bus ride. Our website has more information on <a href="https://www.kch.nhs.uk/patientsvisitors/getting-to-kings/public-transport" target="_blank">getting to King's by train</a><strong>. By bus:</strong> A number of bus routes stop directly outside the hospital on Denmark Hill as well as on Coldharbour Lane. Our website has more information on <a href="https://www.kch.nhs.uk/patientsvisitors/getting-to-kings/public-transport" target="_blank">getting to King's by bus</a>. <strong>By car:</strong> The entrance to King's car park and drop-off point is on Caldecot Road, off Coldharbour Lane. Our website has more information on <a href="http://www.kch.nhs.uk/patients/getting-here/road">getting to King's by road</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There is very limited car parking at King's Denmark Hill site and nearby, so we recommend you use public transport or a taxi to travel here, or ask a friend or relative to drop you at the hospital.</p>
